rook.api.transport

Class GrowableBuffer

  • java.lang.Object
    • rook.api.transport.GrowableBuffer

  • public class GrowableBuffer
extends Object
    A buffer backed by a byte[] array that contains a variable length and can grow as necessary to fit a larger payload
    Author:
    Eric Thill

        public GrowableBuffer reserve(int capacity,
                              boolean keep)
        Resize the underlying buffer to fit the given capacity. Optionally, the existing data in the buffer data can be copied on a resize using keep=true.
        Parameters:
        capacity - Required capacity
        keep - If the existing data in the buffer needs to be kept after a resize.
